</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Beating_Leprosy_Empowering_communities_through_awareness_and_support_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1707745736" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Beating_Leprosy_Empowering_communities_through_awareness_and_support_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1707745736 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Beating_Leprosy_Empowering_communities_through_awareness_and_support_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1707745736 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Beating_Leprosy_Empowering_communities_through_awareness_and_support_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1707745736 320w" width="1467" height="978" alt="Beating Leprosy Empowering communities through awareness and support - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:6deccea9-3ddc-497b-a25f-8e7b53929eaf" title="Beating Leprosy: Empowering communities through awareness and support - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-181_"/><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-182_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by alvarogonzalez

 via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-184_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Leprosy, also known as Hansen's disease, is a chronic infectious disease caused by the bacterium Mycobacterium leprae. Despite being curable and preventable, it continues to affect millions of people worldwide, particularly in regions with limited access to healthcare and education. The physical symptoms of leprosy, such as disfiguring skin lesions and nerve damage, are often exacerbated by the social stigma attached to the disease.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-186_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-187_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-188_">Challenging stigma
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breaking_the_silence_Addressing_Leprosy_stigma_and_discrimination_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1707745890" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breaking_the_silence_Addressing_Leprosy_stigma_and_discrimination_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1707745890 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breaking_the_silence_Addressing_Leprosy_stigma_and_discrimination_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.png?v=1707745890 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breaking_the_silence_Addressing_Leprosy_stigma_and_discrimination_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1707745890 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breaking_the_silence_Addressing_Leprosy_stigma_and_discrimination_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1707745890 320w" width="1792" height="1344" alt="Breaking the silence Addressing Leprosy stigma and discrimination - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:4cdde942-0bdf-45e1-80b5-5db1f54e414b" title="Breaking the silence: Addressing Leprosy stigma and discrimination - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-190_"/><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-191_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by wanaktek via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-193_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">One of the primary goals of World Leprosy Day is to challenge the stigma and discrimination associated with leprosy. Organisations like The Leprosy Mission, American Leprosy Missions, and the Leprosy Association UK work tirelessly to raise awareness, provide support services, and advocate for the rights of individuals affected by leprosy. By educating communities and promoting empathy and understanding, we can create a world where leprosy is not a source of fear or prejudice.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-195_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-196_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-197_">Early detection and treatment
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Supporting_Leprosy_patients_The_role_of_global_health_organisations_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1707746168" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Supporting_Leprosy_patients_The_role_of_global_health_organisations_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1707746168 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Supporting_Leprosy_patients_The_role_of_global_health_organisations_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1707746168 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Supporting_Leprosy_patients_The_role_of_global_health_organisations_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1707746168 320w" width="1321" height="1321" alt="Supporting Leprosy patients The role of global health organisations - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:9665efe2-881f-4f43-a697-29c137d67465" title="Supporting Leprosy patients: The role of global health organisations - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-199_"/><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-200_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by microgen via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-202_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Early detection and treatment are crucial in preventing the progression of leprosy and minimising its impact on individuals and communities. The World Health Organisation (WHO) and the International Federation of Anti-Leprosy Associations (ILEP) support initiatives aimed at improving access to healthcare services, conducting medical research, and developing innovative solutions for leprosy control and care. Through collaborative efforts, we can ensure that no one affected by leprosy is left behind.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-204_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-205_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-206_">Promoting social inclusion
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Advocating_for_change_Promoting_social_inclusion_for_Leprosy_patients_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1707746333" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Advocating_for_change_Promoting_social_inclusion_for_Leprosy_patients_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1707746333 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Advocating_for_change_Promoting_social_inclusion_for_Leprosy_patients_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.png?v=1707746333 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Advocating_for_change_Promoting_social_inclusion_for_Leprosy_patients_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1707746333 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Advocating_for_change_Promoting_social_inclusion_for_Leprosy_patients_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1707746333 320w" width="1766" height="1179" alt="Advocating for change Promoting social inclusion for Leprosy patients - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:7ef77896-579d-4341-bcbd-bd66e5c5c0fc" title="Advocating for change: Promoting social inclusion for Leprosy patients - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-208_"/><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-209_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by LightFieldStudios via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-211_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">World Leprosy Day serves as a reminder that everyone deserves to be treated with dignity and respect, regardless of their health status. Organisations like the Royal Society of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene (RSTMH) advocate for social inclusion and support for individuals affected by leprosy, emphasising the importance of rehabilitation, education, and economic empowerment. By breaking down barriers and fostering inclusivity, we can build a more compassionate and equitable society.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-213_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-214_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-215_">Conclusion</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Early_detection_saves_lives_The_importance_of_timely_Leprosy_diagnosis_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1707746554" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Early_detection_saves_lives_The_importance_of_timely_Leprosy_diagnosis_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1707746554 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Early_detection_saves_lives_The_importance_of_timely_Leprosy_diagnosis_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1707746554 320w" width="999" height="1498" alt="Early detection saves lives The importance of timely Leprosy diagnosis - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:b57cfd57-d9b4-4ce5-a6ee-d7b0ff99e771" title="Early detection saves lives: The importance of timely Leprosy diagnosis - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-217_"/><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-218_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by oneinchpunchphotos via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-220_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">As we commemorate World Leprosy Day, let us reaffirm our commitment to standing in solidarity with those affected by leprosy. Let us amplify their voices, challenge stigma, and advocate for a world where everyone has access to quality healthcare and opportunities for a fulfilling life. Together, we can beat leprosy and build a future of hope and dignity for all.
